# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is customized by the app using the library; however, for an app, you might want to pack
#   it in 
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in cases where the author of a library or package has a requirements.txt, they can
#   ignore Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
